  "texts": [
    "The term was created by Ashton to highlight the potential of using the Internet to link Radio-Frequency Identification (RFID) tags used in corporate supply chains to count and monitor things without the assistance of humans (Li, Xu, and Zhao 2015; Attaran 2017).",
    "By continuously updating data, IoT enables DT applications to create a real-time virtual representation of a physical object.",
    "Therefore, IoT is the primary technology used in all DT applications (Attaran and Celik 2023).",
    "For example, real-time gathered from smart infrastructure enables the authorities to monitor and manage the structures more efficiently.",
    "This can lead to improved building efficiency, reduced traffic congestion, better management of natural resources, and enhanced public safety."
  ],
